description:
&lt;p&gt;If you are a dynamic, enthusiastic Occupational Therapist who is committed to the delivery of robust, evidence based and recovery-focussed OT assessment and interventions, we warmly welcome your application for this exciting post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is based within an established occupational therapy service, delivering a comprehensive service within the Mental Health Unit, Royal Glamorgan Hospital, Llanstrisant. The Occupational Therapy Team Lead role is supported by a Band 6 post, a rotational Band 5 post and a Band 3 Occupational Therapy Support Worker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post offers the opportunity to deliver OT specific assessment and intervention - working with the base, service users&#39; homes and community sites as appropriate. Service delivery follows the Model of Human Occupation (MOHO) model.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a wide range of professional development opportunities and the opportunity to be involved in service evaluation and development - including audit, quality improvement initiatives and research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 17/11/2020 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Angela Arentsen&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Principal Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Angela.Arentsen@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01443 443443 Ext 75647 &lt;/p&gt;
